A week ago:

I was just here this morning, and had to write a review immediately. The menu is super good here, and the food even better. And it doesn't feel like a rip-off. I got two items, spent about $16, and it was a lot of food/drink!

I ordered: the avocado toast with soft-boiled egg on Rye. It was not soggy at all (like I read on another review) - easy to fix this by the fact that you pick your bread. I had it on Rye, and soooo good!! Also, packaged very well for to-go orders.

I ordered a fresh pressed juice as well. The "D" has apple, orange, carrot, and beet. I may be missing a few ingredients, but it was so well-balanced, and I drank it before I got home.

It's a small cafe with a few tables.< /review><Time>1622221315935</Time>< user_id>

This place is charming and delicious. There is an impressive selection of juices, sandwiches and other food options. 115280555622617310747<//userid>
<username>S L-R<//username>< date>
1513975832055<//date>
< text>
I was pleasantly surprised with this place. I got two generous sized pieces of toasted bread with avocado, provolone, and bacon. They were delicious and filling.

The place was empty except for three old men and I think they were owners or related to the people working there. No wait, served immediately.

Small place, better for take out, will not fit large groups. Maybe 4 tables max with 2 seats each.

I'd go again, and it was worth the price. I don't know how much an avocado costs in California, but where I live you'd pay $7 for that much avocado anyway not including the bread and the cheese and the bacon and you'd still have to make it yourself!

Skip the smoothie though, that's a waste of money. It was boring and tasteless.

But the toast is yummy. I hope this place stays around long enough for me to visit again my next business trip.<//text>

Okay let me start by saying the customer service here is AMAZING!!! The employees are so sweet, generous, and patient. I walked in and spent 10 minutes trying to decide what I wanted because everything looked so good and there were so many options! They even said that if any of the items were low on food or finished, they can make more (and this was right before closing so they really didn‚Äôt need to be this generous). Now on to the DELICIOUS food!! They packed all our trays past the brim and it was all for less than $8!!!!! It was definitely like five pounds of food per tray, and the price blew my mind. I was so excited to try everything, and every taste exceeded my expectations! The food was AMAZING from the chow mein to the fried rice to the broccoli beef to the curry chicken. My mouth is watering just thinking about it again. Absolutely loved this location, they deserve all the customers in the world! Thank you for such a good experience, will be back very soon!!!< /Review>

Honestly one of my favorite fast Chinese food go to spots. You get in, get a lot of what you want, and you pay a great price. What more could you ask for? I am currently in a wheelchair because I cannot walk and I had hip replacement surgery to hopefully fix my situation. This place was recommended to me by a friend and I couldn't be happier. Ms. Emma was so kind. I'm glad she was the first point of contact, as I had never been here prior. I don't quite understand the negative reviews, so I will assume that previous staff members no longer work here. My experience was great. I did an entire pre-employment screening that consisted of a physical, flu vaccination, TB test and drug screen. They offered me a COVID testing but it was too soon to test for my employer. The young man that helped me out was really nice and treated me like a human and not just another number. I have worked in an emergency room and know how staff can get. Not here. Don't let the negative reviews sway you. I will gladly come back for another visit.< /Text>

This is my favorite dish when I go to Korean Chinese restaurants. It is impossible to mess up this bad. Maybe Mr Paik should visit these restaurants in SolCal.</text>

< user_id>
115620145790219879247<//user_id>
< text>
Here is self service, so you need to order at the counter and when they call your last two digit# on the receipt you need to pick it up from the counter.

HongKong BanJum which is famous for JjamBbong in S. Korea was started by JongWon Baek.

There are a lot of branches in S.Korea and recently, he has been trying to expand more chains in US.

The Broth for JjamBbong made by sea foods and fresh vegitables with hot peppers, so the soup has a hearty and spicy flavor.

When you eat JjamBbong, try to eat with TangSuYuk which is sweet and sour pork.

It would be perfect matching.

There is JjaJangMyun which is black-bean-sauce noodles but it is a little bit sweet.

When you want to eat spicy soup or try to relieve a hangover, please try to order JjamBbong.

I 've been following hostess of this restaurant, so I know well about the
history of this branch.

I met her first time in food court in
Freshia Market at Garden Grove a few years ago, when she opened it.

I really loved to eat JjamBbong at that time.
However, Freshia Market was bankrupt, so they could not continously do
the business there.

After that, she opened new branch
at Arirang Market at Fullerton,
so I started to visit there to eat JjamBbong.

Finally, she opened new branch at
Village Circle on Beach at Buena Park
which is nearby my house
and located in independent building.

Anyway, I been following her to
eat this delicious JjamBbong.
Now I can enjoy it without any
concern of closing.

Try to eat JjamBbong which is
spicy and delicious.

You will love it when you are addicted
spicy food.< /text>

<date>1471922836472< /date><Rate>4< /Rate><text>Paik's Noodle is in the H Mart plaza right next to 85 Degrees Bakery.
It's a small eatery, but there's an outdoor patio with plenty of seatings.
It's a "fast food" style restaurant. You place order and pay at the counter.
When the food is ready they'll call your number to pick up the food.

Dr. P ordered jjamppong - spicy noodle soup with seafood.
I had a bite. It was really spicy.

Jajangmyeon was very good.
Love the chewy noodle with the black bean sauce.
There are pork and tons of vegetables in the sauce.

Great place for fast and cheap Korean noodle!</text>< pictures>

< Review>
Breakfast burrito was good. Chorizo was spicy. Salsa was very spicy. Literally, it seem to be pureed peppers and oil. But it was good on the breakfast burrito. Sour cream was extra but a nice addition. Pros is that it's open early in the morning but this isn't my favorite breakfast burrito spot in the South Bay. That would still have to be Cafe rosalena.

Cons: somewhat Spartan interior, although that didn't phase me at all. No salsa bar, chips and salsa are extra. Also there are no free refills. I found out the hard way when I went to go pay my bill.< /Review>

I've passed by many times and wanted to stop by. Tonight I finally did, and the food was great. One of my picks for the first time at many taquerias is a carnitas burrito. Their's is just spicy enough, nice and moist. The tortillas are hand made, and grilled so the cheese is nice and soft.

<user_id>109116435742172370324<//user_id><Name>Kolin314<//Name><Time>1570083220579<//Time><rating>5<//rating>< Text>
The whole experience at Arborview is very comfortable. From the office staff, the hygienist, dental assistants and of course Dr. Chen and Dr. Cao. I have never felt like I was an income opportunity, but rather treated as a person and advised what dental work should be considered, but never pressed.  Every procedure I have had was done with excellent care and the most hi-tech equipment and processes.  On their website they say they moved to Roseville after dental school to start a dental practice and a family.  Well they definitely bring the sense of family into their practice. Everyone is very calm and kind.  The last time I was in for dental work I needed a crown replaced on a back molar.  This procedure usually takes at least two if not three office visits. That means time off work.  To my surprise, Dr. Chen prepared the tooth, then used a special 3D camera to map my tooth and then transferred the image data to a milling machine in  another room in the office.  Within a few minutes the crown was ready and installed. I was simply amazed and grateful. I was in and out in about 90 minutes. The procedure was painless.  I have tried several dentists in the area, and frankly I always felt like any of the treatment plans I was offered were about extracting as much money as possible from me. I hated going to the dentist because I knew I was going to have to deal with the high pressure sales people. I found Arborview about 5 years ago and no longer feel the dred of going to the dentist.  My wife and daughter also enjoy the services they provide.<//Text>

<rate>5< /rate><review>We arrived on a holiday weekend at about 5pm and had to wait for about 20 minutes to be seated. Our seat was on the upper patio in the shade (we were given the option to pick). The host who seated us was friendly. Our server promptly greeted us and was very genuine and kind. He told us the specials and gave us his recommendations. The menu had a lot of seafood but also steaks, pastas, sandwiches, a burger, and other choices for a great variety. I had the Mai Tai which was delicious. I also ordered the Ribeye which was one of the recommendations and it was delicious. The complimentary bread was soft and flavorful. The food was all a great value for the price our service remained top notch with our order all coming out in a timely manner. I would definitely recommend checking Tony P's out if you are in Marina Del Rey.</review>< gmapID>

This place is fantastic - food, service, atmosphere!

We went for happy hour, so we ordered potato skins, sliders, Mac n cheese, nachos, and some drinks.  Every item was a decent serving and tasted great.  Their drinks were also good! They don't rip you off on the alcohol.  I also liked that their happy hour menu had many items to choose from.  It's disappointing when there's only 3 items to pick from at other places- not the case here.

I would 100% go again especially because I got to watch the Dodger game! And easy to find street parking.</text>

< review>
This place is fantastic - food, service, atmosphere!

We went for happy hour, so we ordered potato skins, sliders, Mac n cheese, nachos, and some drinks.  Every item was a decent serving and tasted great.  Their drinks were also good! They don't rip you off on the alcohol.  I also liked that their happy hour menu had many items to choose from.  It's disappointing when there's only 3 items to pick from at other places- not the case here.

I would 100% go again especially because I got to watch the Dodger game! And easy to find street parking.</review>

<rate>4< /rate>< review>
This place has a great atmosphere, friendly service, and great views if you're in the dining section. My husband went to watch the NBA final game last night, and had a great time. We sat in the bar area, which was buzzing with excited sports fans. We ate during happy hour, and while the appetizers were only $7.95, the food was a bit bland, but we didn't have any entrees, so I couldn't speak for any signature dishes. Overall, it was enjoyable and my husband and son mentioned a few more times today, how much they enjoyed the crowd and staff at Tony P's. Definitely recommend, but maybe try a seafood dish, which I'm sure will be better than the nachos, spinach- artichoke dip, and calamari. The quesadilla was decent and so were the potato skins.< /review>

< Rate>
4</Rate>
< Review>
This place has a great atmosphere, friendly service, and great views if you're in the dining section. My husband went to watch the NBA final game last night, and had a great time. We sat in the bar area, which was buzzing with excited sports fans. We ate during happy hour, and while the appetizers were only $7.95, the food was a bit bland, but we didn't have any entrees, so I couldn't speak for any signature dishes. Overall, it was enjoyable and my husband and son mentioned a few more times today, how much they enjoyed the crowd and staff at Tony P's. Definitely recommend, but maybe try a seafood dish, which I'm sure will be better than the nachos, spinach- artichoke dip, and calamari. The quesadilla was decent and so were the potato skins.<//Review>

1520093698781< /time>
< Rating>
4<//Rating>
< Review>
Gave it four stars because the server was not all that good. He came pretty quickly once we sat down but we got our food and asked for some hot sauce and it literally took him about 15-20 min to come back with it. We had finished our drinks and half our plates by the time he got back. This was on a slow night.

That aside, he was still a pretty nice guy and the food was incredible! We ordered the Spicy Louisiana plate and the Tilapia with baked potato. Both plates were exceptional. Prices were about average, Maybe even fair in comparison to what you might expect in Marina Del Rey.

Overall, I say at least give this place a try.
P.S. ~ lots of beer and drinks on hand!</Review>

<Text>An institution in Marina del Rey. Nice outdoor eating space. The menu is pretty typical - steaks, fish, salads, pizza. There is an extensive selection of beers. Service is generally good. Almost everything is garlicky, even when a "no garlic" request is made. The fish is often frozen - ask if you want something fresh and local. (Salmon is farmed, not wild, and comes from either the Pacific Northwest or the Atlantic.) The food is fine, but not spectacular. We eat here often because Grandma loves it, and she can get her bourbon. I like the bouillabaisse and the quinoa and beet salad.< /Text>< userid>

< Review>
I've been coming here since before it was Tony P when it was Charlie Brown's. This is always a nice place to visit.  Food is always will prepare and the view from the deck is beautiful. It's located inside Marina del Rey and is a great jumping off point for a nice scenic drive through the marina. Drinks are always good and a bar is located on site.  Staff is friendly and generous and they have nastalgic photos of the marina before it becomes a busy mess.  I lived local for many decades and live in another state now but always come here when I am in town.< /Review>

< Review>
An institution in Marina del Rey. Nice outdoor eating space. The menu is pretty typical - steaks, fish, salads, pizza. There is an extensive selection of beers. Service is generally good. Almost everything is garlicky, even when a "no garlic" request is made. The fish is often frozen - ask if you want something fresh and local. (Salmon is farmed, not wild, and comes from either the Pacific Northwest or the Atlantic.) The food is fine, but not spectacular. We eat here often because Grandma loves it, and she can get her bourbon. I like the bouillabaisse and the quinoa and beet salad.< /Review>

<date>1342941939754< /date><Rate>5</Rate>< Text>
As a couple that frequents restaurant's on a very regular basis, I must say that Tony P's really is one of the best all around places to really enjoy. Everything from the parking to the ambiance, the food and most importantly the staff is great. My wife and I have always enjoyed our time at Tony P's. We have been most fortunate to have one of the of the nicest servers on our several recent visits, by the name of Kalie M, who truly adds to our evening. Kalie is so personalbe and truly is concerned that you are having a great meal.  Everything about the place is EASY and friendly. The staff always accommodates us with a smile. If for instance I need a refill or something of that nature, and our server is occupied elsewhere, undoubtedly there is someone at your service. You don't get "it's not my table" attitude.Truly what all restaurants should strive to be. Very well priced offering a very diverse menu. Take the whole family or just a romantic dinner for two over looking the fabulous yachts in the marina. Thank you Tony P's!!<//Text>

< Text>
Had dinner at Tony P's.  The hotel I was staying at recommended it.  This place was great.  I wanted seafood, and it was delicious!!  Fish was fresh and tasty, appetizer was good, and the tab for three people was very reasonable.   Staff was friendly and helpful with any questions on food or drink.

Tony P's was located on the marina, the view and ambiance were excellent.  You will love their selection of food on the menu, and it isn't too pricy like some of the restaurants in the area.

A definite recommend.  You will be glad you ate there.<//Text>

< rating>
2< /rating>
< review>
The food is mediocre at best- they definitely are relying on their great view of the marina to get people to come in, because it isn‚Äôt the food.
I ordered the fish and chips and added a wedge salad for $4.75. The wedge salad was just lettuce, tomato, and watery blue cheese. When I asked about the onions and the bacon the server said that isn‚Äôt available on the add-on wedge, only the appetizer wedge ($10.95). Nowhere on the menu does it call that out. The flavor really comes from those components mixing with the others. I would recommend skipping the add-on wedge- it was flavorless. It didn‚Äôt even have blue cheese crumbles to help boost the flavor.
Two people at my table ordered the French Onion Soup and they described it as ‚Äúunderwhelming.‚Äù
The fish and chips were decent- not a ton of flavor but tasted fresh, the breading was a little doughy. I substituted the fries for veggies- the veggies were good and you get a large portion (I bet if they scaled down their veggie portion slightly they‚Äôd be able to afford to put some onions and bacon on the wedge salad :) )
Someone at my table had the mahi-mahi and really enjoyed it.
Another person in my party had the salmon- it was cooked nicely but again did not have a lot of flavor.
Our server at the end of the meal explained that an 18% gratuity was added on because ‚ÄúI have to split the tips with my co-workers.‚Äù That really left a bad taste in our mouths because when I said ‚Äúyou have to split it from this table?‚Äù He said ‚Äúyeah we have to tip out.‚Äù I worked as a server through high school and college- tipping out is par for the course. At every restaurant I‚Äôve worked for there is some form of tipping out your back of house, bar, hostess, bussers, etc. It wasn‚Äôt because we were a large group so he had to split the tips with his co-workers, it‚Äôs because that is what you do as a server since they are the ones helping you satisfy your customers.
Two of the people in our party own a boat in the marina and were looking for another restaurant to frequent nearby, but based on last night‚Äôs experience will not be returning to Tony P‚Äôs.< /review>
<Pictures>None</Pictures><response>{'time': 1555364328305, 'text': 'HI Amy, thanks for coming into Tony P\'s. I am sorry about the confusion on the wedge salad. We do offer 2 different wedge salads. One is an add on to an entree (Iceburg wedge, tomatoes, red onions and dressing. $4.75) and one is on the entree salad section (Iceburg wedge, tomatoes, red onions, smoked bacon, crumbled blue cheese and dressing $10.95). We will retrain the salad cook who needs to stir the blue cheese dressing that we make in house, that is full of chunks of blue cheese. I apologize that you didn\'t get that. Regarding the 18% gratuity which is added on to parties of 6 or more. The server didn\'t do a very good job of explaining it to you. Like most restaurants, we add gratuity to tables of 6 or more people. Since you were a server before you understand this policy. Please e-mail me your server\'s name (tony@tonyps.com) and what time you came in. If you do not agree with the added gratuity, please let the manager know and we would take it off.  Our servers "tip out" to the Bussers, Food Runners and Bartenders that help them service your table. They do not share their tips with any other servers. All of this should not have anything to do with you getting great service when you come in. It is all house keeping issues on our side of the restaurant business and I am sorry if you were inconvenienced. Anytime you come into Tony P\'s, and you are not satisfied with service or food please let our managers know. We want everyone to have a great experience.'}<//response><GmapID>0x80c2ba85ae0c3a05:0x7efbca5f367810ca< /GmapID></record></dataset><record>

< review>
As a couple that frequents restaurant's on a very regular basis, I must say that Tony P's really is one of the best all around places to really enjoy. Everything from the parking to the ambiance, the food and most importantly the staff is great. My wife and I have always enjoyed our time at Tony P's. We have been most fortunate to have one of the of the nicest servers on our several recent visits, by the name of Kalie M, who truly adds to our evening. Kalie is so personalbe and truly is concerned that you are having a great meal.  Everything about the place is EASY and friendly. The staff always accommodates us with a smile. If for instance I need a refill or something of that nature, and our server is occupied elsewhere, undoubtedly there is someone at your service. You don't get "it's not my table" attitude.Truly what all restaurants should strive to be. Very well priced offering a very diverse menu. Take the whole family or just a romantic dinner for two over looking the fabulous yachts in the marina. Thank you Tony P's!!<//review>

<Review>I've come here many times and always have a great time. The outdoor seating is ideal for datenight as there is a view of the marina (there are heat lamps) and all the boats and the marina are lit up. Great to watch the sunset. It is a beautiful ambiance for either a table for two or the whole family.
There is also a bar with lots of beers on tap and the bartenders make great cocktails too! This place is set up with tons of TVs so that every football game is available to watch during the season, or any sport for that matter. I think I come here for every big sport event; football playoffs, basketball plays, Sunday football brunch, and baseball playoffs.
The food is great. I love getting the cajun penne pasta; great portion size for your money and tastes amazing. The fish and chips are the best I think I've ever had and there is a tuxedo cake desert which is a must every time I go here.
The wait staff is very friendly and I don't think I have ever sat long for any help or service. They are attentive and approachable. I highly recommend this place to anyone who lives in the area (or doesn't) or someone visiting and staying near LAX. Won't be disappointed.</Review>< Gmap_id>

< Review>
I've been here several times, and up until last night have gotten decent food and drinks. Last night was awful. The service was so slow - 2 hours for dinner for six people (and the restaurant was not crowded). The cider they brought me was in a bottle that looked like it came from the back of the fridge and had been sitting in there for months - the label was ripped and worn, and the cider tasted like sesame seeds. I got a replacement at no charge, but they really shouldn't have served it at all, it was clearly expired. They served my friend's salad in a bowl that had a huge crack down the side. The waiter declined to take our food order after we told him what appetizer we wanted, even though we were all ready, then took 20 minutes to come back. They got two orders wrong (sides were wrong). It was all around extremely disappointing, I'm not sure I'll ever go back. On top of it, I had digestive distress afterwards, which might have been caused by old crab meat. It's too bad, they have a nice selection of beers on tap.< /Review>

<time>1529972693946<//time>< Review>
I have been coming here for over 15 years! Almost everytime I've been here, the staff is friendly and informed of their menu and selections. Timing to me is important in a restaurant, you don't like to be pushed through and out the door, and this establishment has never done that, actually the opposite there have been several times a group and myself come here and seriously feel like we at grandmas house, relaxing and down to earth environment. Big plus is they have amazing bloody Mary's and they keep a great stock beers (allagash my fav) the food menu is tried and true and they stick to what they're good at. Very refreshing to have this local gem for a good night out to eat. Overall my fav is the surf and turf crab/ or lobster and steak.<//Review>

Seafood ‚ÄúGuac‚Äù Tail

Not much seafood. Lots of avocado and onions.

Ordered:
Salmon and Shrimp Combo
Grilled salmon and grilled garlic shrimp, citrus beurre blanc sauce.

Ordered:
Clam Chowder
OK, this might be the only thing that was worth eating.
